HEADWORD: Chromophore
<hw>Chro"mo*phore</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ color +
<grk>fe`rein</grk> to bear.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Any chemical
group or residue (as <chform>NO2</chform>; <chform>N2</chform>; or
<chform>O2</chform>) which imparts some decided color to the compound of
which it is an ingredient.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

